Created by PLY version 3.11 (http://www.dabeaz.com/ply)

Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statement_list
Rule 2     statement_list -> statement
Rule 3     statement_list -> statement_list statement
Rule 4     statement -> ID EQUALS expression SEMICOLON
Rule 5     statement -> PRINT LPAREN ID RPAREN SEMICOLON
Rule 6     expression -> expression PLUS expression
Rule 7     expression -> expression MINUS expression
Rule 8     expression -> expression TIMES expression
Rule 9     expression -> expression DIVIDE expression
Rule 10    expression -> expression MODULO expression
Rule 11    expression -> expression POWER expression
Rule 12    expression -> MINUS expression
Rule 13    expression -> LPAREN expression RPAREN
Rule 14    expression -> NUMBER
Rule 15    expresssion -> FLOAT
Rule 16    expression -> ID

Terminals, with rules where they appear

DIVIDE               : 9
EQUALS               : 4
FLOAT                : 15
ID                   : 4 5 16
LPAREN               : 5 13
MINUS                : 7 12
MODULO               : 10
NUMBER               : 14
PLUS                 : 6
POWER                : 11
PRINT                : 5
RPAREN               : 5 13
SEMICOLON            : 4 5
TIMES                : 8
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

expression           : 4 6 6 7 7 8 8 9 9 10 10 11 11 12 13
expresssion          : 
program              : 0
statement            : 2 3
statement_list       : 1 3

Parsing method: LALR

